article.headline: Long Beach State 77, UC Davis 73 (OT)
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Cody Pearson sank a layup with 24 seconds left in overtime as Long Beach State beat UC Davis 77-73 on Monday. Pearson's layup put the 49ers up 74-71, but UC Davis' Ryan Moore followed with a layup with 14.8 seconds left. Kevin Houston made two free throws to put Long Beach State up 76-73 with 14 seconds left. Moore then missed an 18-footer with 2.3 seconds remaining, and grabbed the rebound and was fouled. Pearson made one of two free throws to seal the win, finishing with 10 points. It was the fourth straight victory for Long Beach State (7-18), which avenged a 78-74 overtime loss to the Aggies in January. Jibril Hodges led the 49ers with 16 points, including four 3-pointers. Shawn Hawkins and Houston each added 15 points. Fowzi Abdelsamad had 24 points for UC Davis (10-16). Moore added 20 points and Rommel Marentez scored 10 for the Aggies, who have lost seven of their last nine games. The 49ers are tied with UC Riverside for the eighth and final spot in the Big West Tournament. Long Beach State erased a 12 point second-half deficit and tied the game at 66 on Hawkins' two free throws with 17 seconds remaining in regulation. Moore missed a 15-footer as time expired in regulation.
